 MA, in 1635; another John Webster (died 1661), ancestor of the lexicographer Noah Webster, emigrated to Cambridge, MA, <i>c.</i> 1631 and later became one of the founders of the colony of CT, of which he was appointed governor in 1656. Daniel Webster (1782–1852), politician and orator, was born in Salisbury, NH, a descendant of Thomas Webster, a prominent 17th-century citizen of Ipswich, MA, whose family had settled there around 1635, while he was still a child."]},{"name":"Web","meanings":["English: variant of   Webb  ."]},{"name":"Webber","meanings":["English (Devon and Somerset): occupational name for a weaver, from Middle English <i>webber</i>, an agent derivative of   Webb  .","Americanized form of German and Jewish (Ashkenazic)   Weber   ‘weaver’."]},{"name":"Webbe","meanings":["English: variant of   Webb  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"John Webb was born on 12 April 1372, in Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter with Joan White. He died in 1420, in his hometown, at the age of 48."},"et":{"12 April 1372–1420":"12. aprill 1372–1420","1375–Female":"1375–Surnud","1395–1462":"1395–1462","1372–1420":"1372–1420","1420":"1420","1375":"1375","1462":"1462","1395":"1395","12 April 1372":"12. aprill 1372","1372":"1372",", , Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom":"Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Frittenden, Kent, England":"Frittenden, Kent, England"},"fi":{"12 April 1372–1420":"12. huhtikuuta 1372–1420","1375–Female":"1375–Kuollut","1395–1462":"1395–1462","1372–1420":"1372–1420","1420":"1420","1375":"1375","1462":"1462","1395":"1395","12 April 1372":"12. huhtikuuta 1372","1372":"1372",", , Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom":"Warwickshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Frittenden, Kent, England":"Frittenden, Kent, England"},"fr":{"12 April 1372–1420":"12 avril 1372–1420","1375–Female":"1375–Décédée"